    "video_length": "PT4M9S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Imagine a place so dark", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you can&#39;t see the nose on your face.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eyes opened or closed, it&#39;s all the same", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because the sun never shines there.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Up ahead, you see a light.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When you creep in to investigate,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a blue light flits around you.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;I could watch this forever,&quot; you think.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But you can&#39;t", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because the mouth of an anglerfish has just sprung open", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and eaten you alive.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You are just one of many creatures", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at the bottom of the ocean who learn too late", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to appreciate the power of bioluminescence.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Bioluminescence refers to the ability", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of certain living things to create light.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The human body can make stuff", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like ear wax and toe nails,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but these organisms can turn", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "parts of their body into glow sticks.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s like nature made them ready to rave.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Why?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In one way or another,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bioluminescence improves a living thing&#39;s chances of survival.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Take the firefly.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s ability to glow green", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "helps it attract a mate on a warm, summer night,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it&#39;s just one of many living things that can glow.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The railroad worm, Phrixothrix hirtus,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "can light up its body in two colors:", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "red and green.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Would you eat something", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that looks like an airport runway?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Neither would any sensible predator.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The flashing lights keep the worm safe.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then there&#39;s the deep sea shrimp,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Acantherphyra purpurea.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When it feels threatened,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it spews a cloud of glowing goo from its mouth.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Who doesn&#39;t run the other way", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when they&#39;ve just been puked on?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Plus, that puke attracts bigger predators", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who want to eat the shrimp&#39;s enemy.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So what if you can&#39;t bioluminesce?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "No problem!", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There are other ways for living things", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to make bioluminescence work for them,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "even if they weren&#39;t born with the equipment to glow.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s revisit the anglerfish", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "moments before it tried to eat you.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That glowing bait on top of its head?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It comes from a pocket of skin called the esca.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The esca holds bioluminescent bacteria.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The anglerfish can&#39;t glow there by itself,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so it holds a sack of glowing bacteria instead.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Remember the firefly?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It can actually make itself glow.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Inside its lantern are two chemicals,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a luciferin and a luciferase.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When firefly luciferase and luciferin mix together", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the presence of oxygen", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and fuel for the cell, called ATP,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the chemical reaction gives off energy in the form of light.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Once scientists figured out", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how the firefly creates its luciferase and luciferin,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they used genetic engineering", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to make this light-producing reaction", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "occur inside other living things that can&#39;t glow.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For example, they inserted the genes,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or instructions, for a cell", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to create firefly luciferase and luciferin into a tobacco plant.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Once there, the tobacco plant followed the instructions", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "slipped into its DNA and lit up like a Christmas tree.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The beauty of bioluminescence,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "unlike the light from the sun or an incandescent bulb,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is that it&#39;s not hot.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It takes place in a range of temperatures", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that don&#39;t burn a living thing.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And unlike a glow stick,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which fades out as the chemicals inside get used up,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bioluminescent reactions use replenishable resources.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s one reason engineers", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are trying to develop bioluminescent trees.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just think, if planted on the side of highways,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they could light the way, using only oxygen", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and other freely available, clean resources to run.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Talk about survival advantage!", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That could help our planet live longer.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do you find yourself thinking of other ways", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to put bioluminescence to good use?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That glow stick you swing at a rave", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "may help you find a mate,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but how else can bioluminescence improve your survival?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you start thinking in this way,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you have seen the light.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }
    ], 
